  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "As of 2015, the Lockheed Martin F-35 Lightning II is often considered one of the best all-around fighter jets due to its advanced stealth capabilities, versatility, and multi-role functionality. Here are some key features that make the F-35 stand out:\n\n1. **Stealth Technology**: The F-35 has a low radar cross-section, making it difficult to detect by enemy radar systems.\n2. **Sensor Fusion**: It integrates data from multiple sensors to provide the pilot with a comprehensive view of the battlefield.\n3. **Versatility**: Available in three variants (F-35A, F-35B, and F-35C), it can operate from conventional runways, short take-off and vertical landing (STOVL), and aircraft carriers.\n4. **Advanced Avionics**: The aircraft is equipped with state-of-the-art avionics, including the AN/APG-81 AESA radar, which enhances its combat capabilities.\n5. **Supercruise**: Some variants have the ability to supercruise, or sustain supersonic flight without afterburners, which saves fuel and extends range.\n\nHowever, other notable mentions as of 2015 include:\n\n- **F-22 Raptor**: Known for its air superiority and stealth capabilities, though less versatile in multi-role missions compared to the F-35.\n- **Eurofighter Typhoon**: Highly maneuverable and effective in air-to-air combat, used by several European countries.\n- **Dassault Rafale**: A French multi-role fighter with excellent avionics and combat capabilities.\n\nEach of these jets has its strengths and is suited to different operational needs, but the F-35's combination of stealth, sensor fusion, and versatility makes it a strong candidate for the title of the best all-around fighter jet as of 2015.",
